  "prompt": "What is the best drama (genre) movie?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" drama movie is highly subjective and can vary based on personal taste, cultural impact, and critical acclaim. However, some films are frequently cited as among the best in the drama genre. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont, this film tells the story of a banker sentenced to life in Shawshank State Penitentiary for a crime he didn't commit. It's celebrated for its themes of hope and friendship.\n\n2. **Schindler's List (1993)** - Steven Spielberg's powerful historical drama about Oskar Schindler, who saved more than a thousand Polish Jews during the Holocaust, is often praised for its emotional depth and moral complexity.\n\n3. **Parasite (2019)** - Directed by Bong Joon-ho, this South Korean film blends drama, thriller, and dark comedy to satirize class disparities. It won multiple Academy Awards, including Best Picture.\n\n4. **Forrest Gump (1994)** - Starring Tom Hanks, this film explores the life of a simple man who inadvertently influences major historical events in the 20th century while exploring themes of love, loss, and perseverance.\n\n5. **The Godfather (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this classic examines the powerful Italian-American crime family in the post-World War II era and is often regarded as one of the greatest films in cinema history.\n\nUltimately, the best drama movie for you may depend on your personal preferences!",
